@node HOWDY "The Tag Thing:  The What?!"

@{u}@{b}Introduction:@{ub}@{uu}
  The Tag Thing is a sort of tagline chooser/inserter.  However, it isn't
limited to taglines; it could also be used for HTML or AmigaGuide tags, or
who knows what else.  Likewise, it isn't fussy about where the tags are sent,
instead relying on external commands or scripts to handle the actual
insertion.  In this way The Tag Thing can support virtually any program, even
those which don't yet exist.  :-)

  TheTagThing evolved from TermTag, an ARexx tagline chooser/inserter I wrote
for use with Olaf Barthel's Term.  With two registered users (thanks Phil and
Greg!) it's been my most financially successful program to date.  Therefore, I
was persuaded to produce a more powerful GadTools-based version.  I can't be
bought, but I @{i}can@{ui} be leased.  :-)


@{u}@{b}Features:@{ub}@{uu}
  * Font-sensitive, resizable, style guide compliant GUI.
  * Tagline insertion is handled by external commands, thus virtually any
   program could be supported.  Currently there are ARexx scripts supporting:
      - Term.
      - YAM.
      - Digital Quill.
      - XDME.
      - Edge.
      - Ed (yes, @{u}that@{uu} Ed :-) ).
      - Cygnus Ed.
      - C-Net.
      - The clipboard.
  * Random tagline selection.
  * Search forwards and backwards with support for AmigaDOS wildcards.
  * Multiple undo/redo.
@endnode


@node NEEDS "The Tag Thing:  Requirements"

@{u}@{b}Required:@{ub}@{uu}
  - Workbench 2.04 or higher.

  Some of the plug-ins may have requirements of their own, such as the
TagToClip.rexx script, which uses ClipWrite (included) to send the tagline to
a clipboard unit.


@{u}@{b}Recommended:@{ub}@{uu}
  - @{b}ARexx@{ub} - Generally, the plug-ins which insert the chosen tagline are
           ARexx scripts.

  - @{b}Cycle To Menu@{ub} or @{b}MCP@{ub} - Drop-down menus for cycle gadgets.
  - @{b}New Edit@{ub}, @{b}MCP@{ub}, or @{b}MultiCX@{ub} - Clipboard support and better editing for string
                               gadgets.
@endnode


