@node STUFFIT "The Tag Thing:  Installation"
@next TAGFILES

@{u}@{b}In the Archive:@{ub}@{uu}
  @{fg shine}TheTagThing@{fg text}/
    @{"c/" link STUFFC}ClipWrite
    @{"PlugIns/" link STUFFPLUGS}TagToClip.rexx
            TagToCED.rexx    (@{fg shine}updated@{fg text})
            TagToCNet.rexx
            TagToEdge.rexx
            TagToEd.rexx
            TagToQuill.rexx
            TagToTerm.rexx
            TagToXDME.rexx
            TagToYAM.rexx
    @{"SampleTags/" link STUFFSAMPLES}AmigaGuideTags.txt
               HTMLTags.txt  (@{fg shine}updated@{fg text})
               Taglines.txt
    TheTagThing
    TheTagThing.info
    TheTagThing.guide
    TheTagThing.guide.info
    TheTagThing.prefs
  TheTagThing.info


@{u}@{b}Installation:@{ub}@{uu}
  Although it may look as though there's a lot to it, none of the included
files are absolutely necessary in order to use The Tag Thing.  Additionally,
The Tag Thing makes no demands as to where the files are kept.
@endnode

@node STUFFC "The Tag Thing:  Installation - The C Directory"
@toc STUFFIT

  Programs in the "c" directory (currently only ClipWrite), are AmigaDOS
commands which certain scripts may rely on.  Copy them to your "C:" directory
if the script is of use to you, otherwise ignore them.


ClipWrite - A CLI command which copies text to a clipboard unit (unit 0 by
           default).  For full information, get the "ClipRdWr12a.lha" archive
           from Aminet (util/cli) or my Web page.

  Usage:  ClipWrite [UNIT <n>] <text>

  Used by the TagToClip.rexx script.
@endnode


@node STUFFPLUGS "The Tag Thing:  Installation - The PlugIns Directory"
@toc STUFFIT

  The PlugIns directory contains ARexx scripts capable of inserting tags into
various programs.  They may be copied anywhere you see fit; although The Tag
Thing's sample configuration file looks for them in the REXX: directory.

  Included in this release are the following:

TagToCED.rexx <filename>
  - Inserts <flename> into the Cygnus Ed text editor at the current cursor position.
  - Version 1.1.
  - Written by Gerald Schnabel.

TagToClip.rexx <filename> <unit>
  - Copies <filename> to clipboard unit <unit> (defaults to unit 0).
  - Requires ClipWrite.

TagToCNet.rexx <filename> <port>
  - Transmits <filename> to port <port> (port 1 by default).

TagToEd.rexx <filename>
  - Inserts <flename> into the Ed text editor below the current cursor
   position.
  - Written by Gerald Schnabel.

TagToEdge.rexx <filename>
  - Inserts <flename> into the Edge text editor at the current cursor position.
  - Written by Gregory Donner.

TagToQuill.rexx <filename>
  - Inserts <flename> into the Digital Quill text editor at the current cursor
   position.

TagToTerm.rexx <filename>
  - Sends <filename> to Term, and whatever is at the other end of the serial
   connection.

TagToXDME.rexx <filename>
  - Inserts <flename> into the XDME text editor above the current cursor
   position.

TagToYAM.rexx <filename>
  - Inserts <filename> into the currently selected message, after the "-- "
   marker.


@{b}Note:@{ub}  These scripts are general purpose, and can be used outside of The Tag
Thing.
@endnode


@node STUFFSAMPLES "The Tag Thing:  Installation - SampleTags Directory"
@toc STUFFIT
@next STUFFIT

  Files in the SampleTags directory are just text files illustrating possible
uses of The Tag Thing.

  Included in this release are the following:

AmigaGuideTags.txt - AmigaGuide formatting commands.  Enhanced by Gregory
                    Donner.

HTMLTags.txt - HTML 3.2 tags and common Netscape and MS Explorer extensions.
              Written by Gregory Donner.

Taglines.txt - Some silly taglines.
@endnode


@node TAGFILES "The Tag Thing:  Tag Files"
@prev STUFFIT

@{u}@{b}Tag Files:@{ub}@{uu}
  The files used by The Tag Thing are regular ASCII text files.  The length of
each line is limited to 256 characters, and the total number of lines is
limited to 65,535.

  The characters "@{b}\n@{ub}" will be interpreted as a linefeed (ASCII 10) when sent.
This can be prevented by using a double backslash, "@{b}\\ @{ub}".

The line:  "To be,\nOr not to be." will be output as:
  To be,
  Or not to be.

While "This \\n won't be sent as a line feed." will look like:
  This \n won't be sent as a linefeed.
@endnode


@node CONFIGFILE "The Tag Thing: Configuration File"

@{u}@{b}Configuration File:@{ub}@{uu}
  The configuration file determines what methods of output will be available in
the @{"Output Mode" link GUI_SEND} cycle gadget.  There will always be at least one output option
available, "Output File", which just writes the chosen tag to the output file.


The format for the configuration files is: <@{b}name@{ub}>, <@{b}command@{ub}>.
  <name> will appear in the @{"Output Mode" link GUI_SEND} cycle gadget.
  <command> will be run when the @{"Send" link GUI_SEND} button is pressed.  Use "@{b}%f@{ub}" for the
name of the output file.

Blank lines and anything following a semicolon (";") are ignorred.


@{b}Example configuration:@{ub}
;  A configuration file might look someting like this:

Term, SYS:RexxC/Rx REXX:TagToTerm.rexx %f
YAM, SYS:RexxC/Rx REXX:TagToYAM.rexx %f

; This will display the tagline in a window.
Window, C:Type >"CON:10/10/600/70/TheTagThing Output/CLOSE/WAIT" %f

; To make some noise:
Speech, C:Type >SPEAK: %f  ; The tag will be spoken.


; Copy to the clipboard:
Clip Unit 0, SYS:RexxC/Rx REXX:TagToClip.rexx %f 0
Clip Unit 1, SYS:RexxC/Rx REXX:TagToClip.rexx %f 1
Clip Unit 5, SYS:RexxC/Rx REXX:TagToClip.rexx %f 5

;
; Text Editors:
;
Quill, SYS:RexxC/Rx REXX:TagToQuill.rexx %f
XDME, SYS:RexxC/Rx REXX:TagToXDME.rexx %f
Edge, SYS:RexxC/Rx REXX:TagToEdge.rexx %f


@{b}Notes:@{ub}
  * It's a good idea to include the full path of the command, as programs run
  from Workbench don't have any search-path information.

  * Some plug-in scripts may have extra options or require certain commands or
   libraries to function.  Load them into a text viewer; all scripts should
   have some documentation at the top of the file explaining their usage.
@endnode


@node PLUGINS "The Tag Thing:  Plug-Ins"

@{u}@{b}Plug-Ins:@{ub}@{uu}
  Plug-ins are the commands or scripts which do the actual work of transferring
the chosen tagline to where you want it to go.


When the @{"Send" link GUI_SEND} button is pressed the following happens:
  o The output file is opened.
   o If the "LF Before Tag" option is in effect then a linefeed is written.
   o The chosen tag line is written.
   o A linefeed is written if the "LF After Tag" option is enabled.
   o The contents of the signature file are copied to the output file if the
     Use Signature gadget is checked.
  o The output file is closed.
  o A command, the plug-in, is run, based on the @{"Output Mode" link GUI_SEND} cycle gadget's
    setting.
  o The Tag Thing may quit or iconify itself, or not, depending on whether the
    @{"Iconify After Send" link MENU_AS} or {"Close After Send" link MENU_AS} menu options are set.


  The only requirement for a plug-in is that it accepts a text file as an
argument.  Thus, a plug-in may be a simple AmigaDOS Type command, an elaborate
(or not) ARexx script, or a whole other program.


  The plug-in may modifiy, delete, fold, spindle, or mutilate the supplied
file as it sees fit.  Other than creating it, The Tag Thing never does anything
with the file.


  The plug-in need not worry about disposing of the text file (although it
may); The Tag Thing has a Delete Tag On Exit option which the user may enable
to deal with this.
@endnode


@node STARTMEUP "The Tag Thing:"

@{u}@{b}Startup Options:@{ub}@{uu}
  The following options may be used as ToolTypes or CLI arguments.  All are
optional.

@{u}Keyword           @{uu} @{u}CLI Shortcut@{uu}  @{u}Argument      @{uu}  @{u}Default Setting                 @{uu}
@{"TAGFILE          " link OPT_TAGF} <blank>       File name       None.
@{"LEFTEDGE         " link OPT_POS} X             0 - 65535       0
@{"TOPEDGE          " link OPT_POS} Y             0 - 65535       0
@{"WIDTH            " link OPT_DIM} W             0 - 65535       0
@{"HEIGHT           " link OPT_DIM} H             0 - 65535       0
@{"FONT             " link OPT_FONT} F             Font name.      Default screen font.
@{"FONTSIZE         " link OPT_FONT} FS            Point size.     Default screen font size.
@{"PUBSCREEN        " link OPT_PS} PS            Public screen.  Default public screen.
@{"SETTINGS         " link OPT_SET} SET           File name       ENV:TheTagThing.prefs.
@{"DEFAULTDRAWER    " link OPT_DWR} DWR           Path name       PROGDIR:
@{"SIGFILE          " link OPT_SIG} SF            File name       None.
@{"USESIGNATURE     " link OPT_SIG} US            None.           No signature is appended.
@{"OUTPUTFILE       " link OPT_OUTF} OF            File name       T:Tagline.txt
@{"ICONIFIEDLEFTEDGE" link OPT_ICON} IX            0-65535         0
@{"ICONIFIEDTOPEDGE " link OPT_ICON} IY            0-65535         0
@{"OPENICONIFIED    " link OPT_ICON} OI            None.           The Tag Thing opens uniconified.
@{"MAXUNDO          " link OPT_UMAX} MU            0 - 2 billion.  10
@{"FINDDIRECTION    " link OPT_FDIR} FD            Keyword.        NONE
@{"LFBEFORETAG      " link OPT_LF} LFB           None.           No linefeed will be inserted.
@{"LFAFTERTAG       " link OPT_LF} LFA           None.           No linefeed will be inserted.
@{"ICONIFYAFTERSEND " link OPT_AS} IAS           None.           Window remains open.
@{"CLOSEAFTERSEND   " link OPT_AS} CAS           None.           Window remains open.
@{"DELETEONEXIT     " link OPT_DOE} DOE           None.           The output file remains.
@{"NOWARNINGS       " link OPT_NW} NW            None.           Warning requesters appear.
@{"NOICONS          " link OPT_NI} NI            None.           Creates an icon when saving.
@endnode


@node OPT_TAGF "The Tag Thing:  Tag File Keyword"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}Tag File Keyword:@{ub}@{uu}

  <blank>, @{b}TAGFILE@{ub} <filename>

  If specified, this file will be loaded and displayed in the listview gadget
when The Tag Thing is started.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  No file is loaded on start-up.
@endnode


@node OPT_POS "The Tag Thing:  Window Position Keywords"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}Window Position Keywords:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}X@{ub}, @{b}LEFTEDGE@{ub} <0 - 65535>
@{b}Y@{ub}, @{b}TOPEDGE@{ub}  <0 - 65535>

  These two keywords set the initial position where The Tag Thing's window will
open.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  0.
@endnode


@node OPT_DIM "The Tag Thing:  Window Dimension Keywords"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}Window Dimension Keywords:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}X@{ub}, @{b}WIDTH@{ub}  <0 - 65535>
@{b}Y@{ub}, @{b}HEIGHT@{ub} <0 - 65535>

  These two keywords set the dimensions of The Tag Thing's window.  These
values may be adjusted to fit the screen size and the minimum space required to
create the GUI.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  0 (Smallest possible size).
@endnode


@node OPT_FONT "The Tag Thing:  Font Keywords"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}Font Keywords:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}F@{ub}, @{b}FONT@{ub} <font name>

  Font to use in The Tag Thing's window.  It isn't necessary to supply the
".font" extension.


@{b}FS@{ub}, @{b}FONTSIZE@{ub} <point size>

  What size the font specified by @{b}FONT@{ub} should be.


@{b}Note:@{ub}  In order to use a custom font, both @{b}FONT@{ub} and @{b}FONTSIZE@{ub} must be specified.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  Default screen font.
@endnode


@node OPT_PS "The Tag Thing:  Public Screen Keyword"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}Public Screen Keyword:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}PS@{ub}, @{b}PUBSCREEN@{ub} <public screen name>

  Name of the public screen to open The Tag Thing's window on.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  Default public screen; usually Workbench.
@endnode


@node OPT_SET "The Tag Thing:  Configuration File Keyword"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}Configuration File Keyword:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}SET@{ub}, @{b}SETTINGS@{ub} <filename>

  File to use for setting the various forms of output.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  ENV:TheTagThing.prefs
@endnode


@node OPT_DWR "The Tag Thing:  Default Drawer Keyword"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}Default Drawer Keyword:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}DWR@{ub}, @{b}DEFAULTDRAWER@{ub} <path>

  Initial path to appear in file requesters if no file name exists.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  PROGDIR:
@endnode


@node OPT_SIG "The Tag Thing:  Signature File Keywords"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}Signature File Keywords:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}SF@{ub}, @{b}SIGFILE@{ub} <filename>

  File containing signature text.


@{b}US@{ub}, @{b}USESIGNATURE@{ub} <filename>

  If specified, when the The Tag Thing sends a tag the signature file will be
appended to the tag.

  Both of these options may be changed via the GUI.  The keywords only
determine the initial settings.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  No signature.
@endnode


@node OPT_OUTF "The Tag Thing:  Output File Keyword"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}Output File Keyword:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}OF@{ub}, @{b}OUPUTFILE@{ub} <filename>

  When the @{"Send" link GUI_SEND} button is pressed The Tag Thing writes the selected tag, and
possibly a signature, to a file.  This keyword specifies the path and name of
that file.

  The output file may also be changed using the @{"Output File" link MENU_OUTF} menu option.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  T:Tagline.txt.
@endnode


@node OPT_ICON "TTManger:  Iconified Keywords"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}Iconified Keywords:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}IX@{ub}, @{b}ICONIFIEDLEFTEDGE@{ub} <0 - 65535>
@{b}IY@{ub}, @{b}ICONIFIEDTOPEDGE@{ub}  <0 - 65535>

  These two keywords specify the location The Tag Thing's window will appear
at when first iconified.


@{b}OI@{ub}, @{b}OPENICONIFIED@{ub}

  If specified, The Tag Thing will open in an iconified state.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  Open the main (uniconified) window.  When iconified, the
         window will be in the upper left corner (0, 0)
@endnode


@node OPT_UMAX "The Tag Thing:  Maximum Undo Levels Keyword"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}Maximum Undo Levels Keyword:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}MU@{ub}, @{b}MAXUNDO@{ub} <0 - 2 billion>

  How many operations The Tag Thing remembers, and may undo.  Setting MAXUNDO to
"0" disables the undo system (don't do this; I spent a lot of time on the undo
routines - use 'em!  :-)  ).


@{b}Default:@{ub}  10
@endnode


@node OPT_FDIR "The Tag Thing:  Initial Find Direction Keyword"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}Initial Find Direction Keyword:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}FD@{ub}, @{b}FINDDIRECTION@{ub} <direction>

  This option sets whether The Tag Thing will automatically perform a search
whenever the pattern in the @{"Find" link GUI_FIND} gadget is changed, and in what direction the
search should be.

  <direction> may be:  NEXT    - A forward search is performed.
                       PREV    - A backwards search is performed.
                       <blank> - No search is automatically performed.


  The search direction may also be set using the @{"Find Direction" link MENU_FDIR} menu items.

@{b}Default:@{ub}  No search is automatically performed.
@endnode


@node OPT_LF "The Tag Thing:  Linefeed Keywords"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}Linefeed Keywords:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}LFB@{ub}, @{b}LFBEFORETAG@{ub}
@{b}LFA@{ub}, @{b}LFAFTERTAG@{ub}

  These keywords specify whether a linefeed (ASCII 10) will be inserted to
produce a blank line above the tagline (LFBEFORETAG) and/or between the tag
and the signature (LFAFTERTAG).

  These options may also be enabled or disabled from the Settings menu.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  No linefeeds are inserted.
@endnode


@node OPT_AS "The Tag Thing:  After Send Keywords"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}After Send Keywords:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}IAS@{ub}, @{b}ICONIFYAFTERSEND@{ub}
@{b}CAS@{ub}, @{b}CLOSEAFTERSEND@{ub}

  These keywords determine what happens after a tagline has been sent.
ICONIFYAFTERSEND will iconify the window, while CLOSEAFTERSEND will end the
program.  Only one of these options may be in effect; if both are specified
then The Tag Thing will ignore the CLOSEAFTERSAVE option.

  These options may also be enabled or disabled from the Settings menu.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  Both of these options are off, and The Tag Thing remains open
         after sending a tag.
@endnode


@node OPT_DOE "The Tag Thing:  Delete On Exit Keyword"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}Delete On Exit Keyword:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}DOE@{ub}, @{b}DELETEONEXIT@{ub}

  If specified, the output file will be deleted when The Tag Thing is
terminated, unless the file was written when the @{"Output Mode" link GUI_SEND} cycle gadget was
set to "Output File".


  This option may also be enabled or disabled by the Delete On Exit menu
option.

@{b}Default:@{ub}  The output file is not deleted.
@endnode


@node OPT_NW "The Tag Thing:  No Warnings Keyword"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}No Warnings Keyword:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}NW@{ub}, @{b}NOWARNINGS@{ub}

  If specified, "Are you sure?" requesters and the like are supressed.

  This option may also be enabled or disabled by the @{"No Warnings" link MENU_WARN} menu
option.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  Warning requesters are enabled.
@endnode


@node OPT_NI "The Tag Thing:  No Icons Keyword"
@toc STARTMEUP
@next STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}No Icons Keyword:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}NI@{ub}, @{b}NOICONS@{ub}

  Specifies whether or not an icon will be created when the tag file is saved.
An icon may also be created when the @{"Output Mode" link GUI_SEND} cycle gadget is set to "Output
File" and the selected tag is sent.

  This option may also be enabled or disabled by the @{"Create Icons" link MENU_ICONS} menu
option.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  Create icons.
@endnode


