@node GUI_TAGF "The Tag Thing - Tag File Gadgets"
@toc THEGUI
           ______________________________  _
Tag File: |Text:Taglines.txt             ||r|
           ------------------------------  -

@{u}@{b}Tag File String Gadget:@{ub}@{uu}
  Entering a file name in this gadget loads that file.  The Tag Thing uses
regular ACSII text files.  See the @{"Tag Files" link TAGFILES} section for more information.


@{u}@{b}Tag File File Requester Button:@{ub}@{uu}
  This gadget pops up a file requester allowing you to load a tag file.
@endnode


@node GUI_QNUM "The Tag Thing - Tag Number Gadgets"
@toc THEGUI
      _____  ___      _____
Tag: |7    ||???| Of |24   |
      -----  ---      -----

@{u}@{b}Tag Number Integer Gadget:@{ub}@{uu}
  This gadget displays the line number of the current tag.  Entering a new
number jumps to that line.


@{u}@{b}Random Tag Button:@{ub}@{uu}
  Pressing this button picks a tag at random.


@{u}@{b}Total Lines Display:@{ub}@{uu}
  This gadget displays the total number of lines in the listview.
@endnode


@node GUI_FIND "The Tag Thing - Search Gadgets"
@toc THEGUI
@next GUI_LV
       _______________  __  __
Find: |*engin*        ||<-||->|
       ---------------  --  --

@{u}@{b}Search Pattern String Gadget:@{ub}@{uu}
  Use this gadget to set the text to search for.  AmigaDOS @{"wildcards" link WILD} may be
used.   If no text is entered a pattern of "#?" (match anything) is used.

   A forward or backwards search may automatically be performed whenever the
pattern is changed by setting the Find Direction @{"startup option" link OPT_FDIR} or
@{"menu items" link MENU_FDIR}.


@{u}@{b}Backwards Search Button:@{ub}@{uu}
  Pressing this button searchs from the current line back to the first for the
current search pattern.


@{u}@{b}Forward Search Button:@{ub}@{uu}
  Pressing this button searchs from the current line to the last for the
current search pattern.
@endnode


@node WILD "AmigaDOS Pattern Matching"
@toc THEGUI
@next WLDPAT

@{u}@{b}Wildcards:@{ub}@{uu}
A brief summary of important AmigaDOS pattern matching wildcards:
(What, you don't already know these?!  :-)  )

#? (or "*", if enabled) - Match any characters.

?                       - Match a single character.

#<p>                    - Match zero or more occurrences of <p>.

~(<p>)                  - Do not match <p>.

(<p1>|<p2>)             - Logical OR - Match <p1> or <p2>

(<char>-<char>)         - Set a character range (e.g. (A-E))
@endnode


@node GUI_LV "The Tag Thing - ListView Gadget"
@toc THEGUI
@prev GUI_FIND

 -----------------------------------------------------
|He's dead, Jim.  Grab his tricorder; I'll get his w|#|
|I was voted most likely to be least likely voted mo| |
|@{bg fill}Q:  How many Microsoft engineers does it take to ch@{bg background}|#|
|If it's 2% milk then what's the other 98%?!        |^|
|I bought a toy poodle, but it died when I tried ins|v|
|-----------------------------------------------------|
|Q:  How many Microsoft engineers does it take to chan|
 -----------------------------------------------------

@{u}@{b}ListView Gadget:@{ub}@{uu}
  The listview displays the available tag lines; allowing you to browse and
select.  The currently selected tag can be edited in the string gadget.
@endnode


@node GUI_EDIT "The Tag Thing - Edit Gadgets"
@toc THEGUI
 ________   ________
|  Add   | | Delete |
 --------   --------

@{u}@{b}Add Button:@{ub}@{uu}
  The Add button inserts a blank line into the listview after the currently
selected tag.


@{u}@{b}Delete Button:@{ub}@{uu}
  The Delete button deletes the currently selected tag.
@endnode


@node GUI_UNDO "The Tag Thing - Undo Gadgets"
@toc THEGUI

 ________   ________
|  Undo  | |  Redo  |
 --------   --------

@{u}@{b}Undo Button:@{ub}@{uu}

  Clicking undo undoes the last operation.  The number of operations which may
be undone is set by the @{"MAXUNDO" link OPT_UMAX} startup option (the default is 10).


@{u}@{b}Redo Button:@{ub}@{uu}

  Redo undoes an undo.  :-)


@{b}Note:@{ub}  The operations which currently may be undone are:
  - Adding a quote to the list (@{"Add" link GUI_EDIT} button).
  - Deleting a quote (@{"Delete" link GUI_EDIT} button).
  - Editing a quote (@{"Listview" link GUI_LV} string gadget).
@endnode


@node GUI_SEND "The Tag Thing - Output Gadgets"
@toc THEGUI
 ______       ____________
| Send | To: |@|  Speech  |
 ------       ------------

@{u}@{b}Send Button:@{ub}@{uu}
  Pressing the Send button writes the selected tag to the default output file
(this can be set via the @{"OUTPUTFILE" link OPT_OUTF} startup option or the Set Output File menu
option).  Then the appropriate command, based on the Output cycle gadget's
current setting, is run (syncronously).


@{u}@{b}Output Mode Cycle Gadget:@{ub}@{uu}
  Specifies the command to execute when the @{b}Send@{ub} button is pressed.  The
contents of this gadget are determined by the @{"configuration file" link CONFIGFILE}.
@endnode


@node GUI_SIG "The Tag Thing - Signature Gadgets"
@toc THEGUI
@next THEGUI
            __  ___________________  _
Signature: |./||TEXT:MySig.txt     ||r|
            --  -------------------  -

@{u}@{b}Use Signature Checkbox Gadget:@{ub}@{uu}
  If checked, the file named in the Signature string gadget will be appended to
the selected tag when the @{"Send" link GUI_SEND} button is pressed.
This gadget may be set at start-up using the @{"USESIG" link OPT_SIG} keyword.


@{u}@{b}Signature File String Gadget:@{ub}@{uu}
  The path and name of a text file to append to a tag.  The Tag Thing doesn't
impose any limits or restrictions as to the length or contents of this file.
The file may be initially set with the @{"SIGFILE" link OPT_SIG} keyword.


@{u}@{b}Signature File File Requester Button:@{ub}@{uu}
  This button brings up a file requester allowing you to choose a file to use
as a signature.
@endnode


