@{u}@{b}Quit@{ub}@{uu}
  Quits The Tag Thing (you were expecting something different? :-)  ).  If
Warnings are enabled, then a requester will pop up asking if you're sure you
want to quit (accidents happen :-)  ).

@{b}Menu Shortcut:@{ub}  <Right Amiga> ?
@endnode


@node MENU_EDIT "The Tag Thing Menus:  Edit - Edit"
@toc MENUS

@{bg shine}@{u}Edit       @{uu}@{bg background}
@{bg shine}Edit      »@{bg background}->@{bg shine}Config   @{bg background}
     :       @{bg shine}Taglines @{bg background}
             @{bg shine}Signature@{bg background}


@{u}@{b}Config@{ub}@{uu}
  Runs the text editor, named in the environment variable @{b}Editor@{ub}, on The Tag
Thing's current configuration file.

@{u}@{b}Taglines@{ub}@{uu}
  The file named in the @{"Tag File" link GUI_TAGF} string gadget is opened for editing.

@{u}@{b}Signature@{ub}@{uu}
  The file named in the @{"Signature File" link GUI_SIG} string gadget is opened for editing.


@{b}Note:@{ub}
  * The environment variable @{b}Editor@{ub} (ENV:Editor), containing the name of your
text editor-of-choice, must be set in order for these menu options to work.

  * The text editor is run asynchronously; The Tag Thing doesn't wait on it.
@endnode


@node MENU_DEL "The Tag Thing Menus:  Edit - Delete"
@toc MENUS

@{bg shine}@{u}Edit       @{uu}@{bg background}
     :
@{bg shine}Delete    »@{bg background}->@{bg shine}All            @{bg shadow}@{fg shine}@{i}A @{ui}@{fg text}@{bg shine}.@{bg background}
     :       @{bg shine}Current To Top @{bg shadow}@{fg shine}@{i}A @{ui}@{fg text}@{bg shine}<@{bg background}
             @{bg shine}Current To End @{bg shadow}@{fg shine}@{i}A @{ui}@{fg text}@{bg shine}>@{bg background}


@{u}@{b}All@{ub}@{uu}
  Deletes all the taglines.  Similar to New, except that the file name isn't
cleared.

@{b}Menu Shortcut:@{ub}  <Right Amiga> .


@{u}@{b}Current To Top@{ub}@{uu}
  Deletes all lines from the current line to the beginning of the list.

@{b}Menu Shortcut:@{ub}  <Right Amiga> <


@{u}@{b}Current To End@{ub}@{uu}
  The current line and all others after it are deleted.

@{b}Menu Shortcut:@{ub}  <Right Amiga> >
@endnode


@node MENU_UNDO "The Tag Thing Menus:  Edit - Undo"
@toc MENUS

@{bg shine}@{u}Edit       @{uu}@{bg background}
     :
@{bg shine}Undo   [A]U@{bg background}
@{bg shine}Redo   [A]Z@{bg background}
@{bg shine}Flush      @{bg background}


@{u}@{b}Undo@{ub}@{uu}
  Undoes the last operation.  The number of operations which may be undone is
set by the @{"MAXUNDO" link OPT_UMAX} startup option (the default is 10).

@{b}Menu Shortcut:@{ub}  <Right Amiga> U


@{u}@{b}Redo@{ub}@{uu}
  Undoes an undo.  :-)

@{b}Menu Shortcut:@{ub}  <Right Amiga> Z


@{b}Note:@{ub}  The operations which currently may be undone are:
  - Adding a quote to the list (@{"Add" link GUI_EDIT} button).
  - Deleting a quote (@{"Delete" link GUI_EDIT} button).
  - Editing a quote (@{"Listview" link GUI_LV} string gadget).


@{u}@{b}Flush@{ub}@{uu}
  Empties the undo buffer.
@endnode


@node MENU_OUTF "The Tag Thing Menus:  Settings - Set Output File"
@toc MENUS

@{bg shine}@{u}Settings                 @{uu}@{bg background}
@{bg shine}Set Output File...       @{bg background}
             :


@{u}@{b}Set Output File@{ub}@{uu}
  When the @{"Send" link GUI_SEND} button is pressed The Tag Thing writes the selected tag, and
possibly a linefeed or two and a signature, to a file.  This file is
T:Tagline.txt by default.  Use this menu option to select a new destination.
The output file may also be set with the @{"OUTPUTFILE" link OPT_OUTF} start-up option.
@endnode


@node MENU_LF "The Tag Thing Menus:  Settings - Linefeeds"
@toc MENUS

@{bg shine}@{u}Settings                 @{uu}@{bg background}
             :
@{bg shine}./ LF Before Tag?        @{bg background}
@{bg shine}   LF After Tag?         @{bg background}
             :


@{u}@{b}LF Before Tag@{ub}@{uu}
  If checked, a linefeed (ASCII 10) will inserted before the tagline, when
sent.

@{u}@{b}LF After Tag@{ub}@{uu}
  This appends a linefeed to the selected tag, when the @{"Send" link GUI_SEND} button is pressed.


@{b}Note:@{ub}  These options may be initially set using the @{"LFBEFORETAG" link OPT_LF} and @{"LFAFTERTAG" link OPT_LF}
start-up keywords.
@endnode


@node MENU_AS "The Tag Thing Menus:  Settings - Post-Send Options"
@toc MENUS

@{bg shine}@{u}Settings                 @{uu}@{bg background}
             :
@{bg shine}./ Iconify After Send?   @{bg background}
@{bg shine}   Close After Send?     @{bg background}
             :


@{u}@{b}Iconify After Send@{ub}@{uu}
  If checked, The Tag Thing will iconify itself after a tag has been
successfully sent.


@{u}@{b}Close After Send@{ub}@{uu}
  The Tag Thing will quit once a tag has been successfully sent if this option
is enabled.


@{b}Note:@{ub}
  * These options are mutually exclusive; only one can be active.

  * These options may be on start-up using the @{"ICONIFYAFTERSEND" link OPT_AS} or
   @{"CLOSEAFTERSEND" link OPT_AS} keywords.
@endnode


@node MENU_DOE "The Tag Thing Menus:  Settings - Delete Tag On Exit"
@toc MENUS

@{bg shine}@{u}Settings                 @{uu}@{bg background}
             :
@{bg shine}./ Delete Tag On Exit?   @{bg background}
             :


@{u}@{b}Delete Tag On Exit@{ub}@{uu}
  If enabled, the output file (T:Tagline.txt by default, although it may be
changed via the @{"OUTPUTFILE" link OPT_OUTF} or @{"Set Output File" link MENU_OUTF} options) will be deleted when The
Tag Thing is exited.


@{b}Note:@{ub}  @{"DELETEONEXIT" link OPT_DOE} be used to enable this feature at startup.
@endnode


@node MENU_FDIR "The Tag Thing Menus:  Settings - Initial Find Direction"
@toc MENUS

@{bg shine}@{u}Settings                 @{uu}@{bg background}
             :
@{bg shine}./ Find Direction:  Next?@{bg background}
@{bg shine}   Find Direction:  Prev?@{bg background}
             :


@{u}@{b}Find Direction:  Next@{ub}@{uu}
@{u}@{b}Find Direction:  Prev@{ub}@{uu}
  These menu options allow a search to be performed when the pattern in the
@{"Find" link GUI_FIND} gadget is changed.  They are mutually exclusive; only one can be checked.
If neither is checked, then no search will be automatically performed.


@{b}Note:@{ub}  The find direction may be set at start-up using the @{"FINDDIRECTION" link OPT_FDIR}
      keyword.
@endnode


@node MENU_WARN "The Tag Thing Menus:  Settings - Warnings"
@toc MENUS

@{bg shine}@{u}Settings                 @{uu}@{bg background}
             :
@{bg shine}./ Warnings?             @{bg background}
             :


@{u}@{b}Warnings@{ub}@{uu}
  This option determines whether warning requesters will appear, asking for
confirmation, before certain actions, such as overwriting an existing file,
quitting the program, or if the taglines have been modified but not yet saved.


@{b}Note:@{ub}  The @{"NOWARNINGS" link OPT_WARN} keyword may be used at start-up to disable warnings.
@endnode


@node MENU_ICONS "The Tag Thing Menus:  Settings - Create Icons"
@toc MENUS
@next MENUS

@{bg shine}@{u}Settings                 @{uu}@{bg background}
             :
@{bg shine}./ Create Icons?         @{bg background}


@{u}@{b}Create Icons@{ub}@{uu}
  If enabled, The Tag Thing will create icons for the files it writes when
@{"Save" link MENU_SAVE} or @{"Save As" link MENU_SAVE} is used.  Also, if the @{"Output Mode" link GUI_SEND} is "Output File" then an
icon will also be created for the output file.


@{b}Note:@{ub}  The creation of icons may be disabled at start-up using the
@{"NOICONS" link OPT_NI} keyword.
@endnode


